# SOLAT TypeScript/React (Desktop) Conventions

When editing or generating TypeScript/React under `apps/desktop/src/`, apply these rules. Output conventions-compliant code or list violations.

## Code style

- **Formatter:** Prettier (via ESLint)
- **Linter:** ESLint with TypeScript rules
- **Line length:** 100 characters

## Naming

- **Component files:** `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `StatusScreen.tsx`)
- **Utility/hook files:** `camelCase.ts` or `useCamelCase.ts` (e.g. `useEngineHealth.ts`)
- **Components:** `PascalCase` (e.g. `StatusScreen`)
- **Hooks:** `use` prefix (e.g. `useEngineHealth`)
- **Types/interfaces:** `PascalCase` (e.g. `HealthData`)

## Components

```typescript
// Props interface defined above component
interface StatusScreenProps {
  health: HealthData | null;
  isLoading: boolean;
}

// Export named function (not default)
export function StatusScreen({ health, isLoading }: StatusScreenProps) {
  // ...
}
```

- Define props interface above the component
- Export named function, not default export
- No `any`; use proper types

## State management

- Use React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useCallback`)
- Extract complex state to custom hooks
- Avoid prop drilling beyond 2 levels

